inux Commands:
=======================================================
Linux Command to create a symbolic link to file or directory
ln -s file1 lnk1

Create a physical link to file or directory
ln file1 lnk1


 View files of directory
ls -F


Move a file or directory
mv dir/file /new_path



 With the help of nice command, users can set or change the priorities of processes in Linux.
 nice
 
 
 To search all files that end in ".conf"
 find /path -type f -name "*.conf"
 
 
 find / -perm 644
 
 
  Prints the number of lines in a file.
 wc -l file_name OR cat file_name | wc -l
 
 
 
 To Create tar Archive File
 tar -cvf compress.tar /path/directory
 
     â€‹c - create a archive file.
    x - extract a archive file.
    v - show the progress of archive file.
    f - filename of archive file.
    t - viewing content of archive file.
    j - filter archive through bzip2.
    z - filter archive through gzip.
    r - append or update files/directories to existing archive file.
    w - verify a archive file.
    
    
    
    
    To Untar tar Archive File
    tar -xvf compress.tar
    
    
    To Untar tar Archive File in a specific directory
    tar -xvf compress.tar -C /path/to diretory
    
    
    Extract Group of Files using Wildcard from tar Archive
    tar -xvf compress.tar --wildcards '*.txt'
    
    
    
    
    About TAR.GZ
    
    To Create tar.gz Archive File
    tar -cvzf compresstar.gz /path/directory
    
    
    To Untar tar.gz Archive File
    tar -zxvf compress.tar.gz
    
    
    Untar Single file from tar.gz File
    tar -zxvf compress.tar.gz file1.txt
    


Commands for ZIP    
    To zipping a file or folder.
zip compress.zip file1 file2 folder1



To Zip individual files to a zip archive

zip compress.zip file1 file2 file3


content of a folder use -r option
zip -r compress.zip Folder


list all the files stored in a zip file
unzip -l compress.zip



Allows write opening of a file only append mode
chattr +a file1



To view your network hostname
uname -n


 scp allows you to secure copy files to and from another host in the network.
 scp -r -P 22 (ssh port) user@source_hostname:/path/to/dir /destination/path
 
 
 tail command
 $ tail -n 4 /etc/passwd
 
 
 $ wc /etc/passwd
 
 
 $ grep nologin /etc/passwd
 

